> Looking for a super quick and tasty midweek dinner option? Try cooking up our Creamy Chicken Breast and Mushroom Pasta in just 15 minutes for a delicious and speedy meal.

Boil a full #kettle{}. Pour it into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat.

Boil the @Rigatoni Pasta{180%grams}, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain and drizzle with @oil{}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, fry the @Diced British Chicken Breast{240%grams}, @Dried Oregano{1%sachet} and @Sliced Mushrooms{120%grams}, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Stir in the @Creme Fraiche{150%grams}, @Wild Mushroom Paste{15%grams} and @Water for the Sauce{100%milliliter}.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat. Simmer, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in the @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{20%grams} and cooked rigatoni until combined.

Share your pasta between your bowls. Enjoy!